### Test Transaction API

### 1. Get all transactions
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Create transaction in USD
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": 0,
  "partyType": 0,
  "partyId": 1,
  "currencyId": 2,
  "originalAmount": 1000.00,
  "notes": "Payment received from customer in USD"
}

### 3. Create transaction in Iranian Rial
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": 1,
  "partyType": 1,
  "partyId": 1,
  "currencyId": 3,
  "originalAmount": 5000000.00,
  "notes": "Payment to supplier in Iranian Rial"
}

### 4. Create transaction in Afghani (base currency)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": 2,
  "partyType": 2,
  "partyId": null,
  "currencyId": 1,
  "originalAmount": 2500.00,
  "notes": "Office rent expense in Afghani"
}

### 5. Get specific transaction
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/1
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Get transactions by party (Customer transactions)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/by-party/customer/1
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Get transactions by party (Supplier transactions)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/by-party/supplier/1
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Get transactions by type (Sale transactions)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/by-type/sale
Content-Type: application/json

### 9. Get transactions by type (Purchase transactions)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/by-type/purchase
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Update transaction notes
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Updated payment notes - customer paid in full"
}

### 11. Delete transaction
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/transactions/1
Content-Type: application/json